==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Catgut
<hw>Cat"gut`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Cat</ets> +
<ets>gut</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A cord of great toughness made
from the intestines of animals, esp. of sheep, used for strings of
musical instruments, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A sort of linen or canvas, with wide
interstices.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Catharine wheel</ent>⟦br⟧
